-- Peru Air Force May Buy 10 Embraer Planes, Brazil Ministry Says
-- B y   R a y m o n d   C o l i t t
-- 2012-02-14T20:31:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/peru-air-force-may-buy-10-embraer-planes-brazil-ministry-says.html
Peru ’s  Air Force  is considering
buying 10 Super Tucano turboprop planes made by  Embraer (EMBR3)  SA, the
world’s fourth-biggest aircraft maker,  Brazil ’s  Defense Ministry 
said.  Both countries will increase their cooperation in
aerospace, including a possible upgrade of Peru’s current fleet
of Tucano aircraft, the ministry said in a statement posted on
its website.  Brazil’s Defense MinisterCelso Amorim met his Peruvian
counterpart Alberto Otarola Penaranda in Brasilia today to
discuss military cooperation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Raymond Colitt in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 rcolitt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
